Two people were killed in an alleged taxi related shooting at KwaDukuza on the KwaZulu-Natal north coast, on Wednesday evening. According to IPSS Medical Rescue spokesperson, Paul Herbst, they were called out to Balcomb Street in the KwaDukuza CBD. “IPSS Medical Rescue, together with Lenmed eThekwini advanced life support paramedics, responded to Stanger for reports of a mass shooting. “On arrival, paramedics established that a taxi related shooting had occurred and one association member had sustained fatal injuries. A second person, a member of the public in his driveway, was unfortunately struck by a stray bullet resulting in critical injuries.” Herbst said advanced life support interventions were carried out on the man and he was taken to hospital, where he died. The circumstances around the shooting are presently unclear. KwaDukuza SAPS confirmed the incident. Updates to follow.